om language mode for ",[301,302,303],"code",{},".pseudo"," files and provides a built-in interpreter that parses and executes the code. Results are displayed in the VS Code output panel.",[25,306,308],{"id":307},"getting-started","Getting Started",[310,311,312,315,321,324],"ol",{},[41,313,314],{},"Install the extension from the VS Code Marketplace",[41,316,317,318,320],{},"Create a new file with the ",[301,319,303],{}," extension",[41,322,323],{},"Write your pseudo code",[41,325,326,327,330],{},"Press ",[301,328,329],{},"Ctrl+Shift+P"," and run \"Pseudo Runner: Execute\"",{"title":97,"searchDepth":98,"depth":98,"links":332},[333,334,335,336],{"id":27,"depth":98,"text":28},{"id":35,"depth":98,"text":36},{"id":295,"depth":98,"text":296},{"id":307,"depth":98,"text":308},"A VS Code extension that runs pseudo code files directly in the editor.","https://github.com/Kratosgado/pseudo-runner",[243,340],"https://image2url.com/r2/default/images/1772468076141-94683d8e-029b-4887-843f-99970e779057.png","https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/publishers/Kratosgado",{},{"icon":116},"/projects/pseudo-runner",{"title":257,"description":337},"pseudo-runner",[82,164],"projects/pseudo-runner","lEtu8O4bKLsBWbALyNK1YCvlh5bJNHejXalx8ZmAo5g",{"id":351,"title":352,"body":353,"coverImage":397,"description":398,"extension":105,"github":399,"images":400,"liveUrl":399,"meta":402,"navigation":403,"path":404,"rank":405,"seo":406,"slug":407,"stack":408,"stem":410,"__hash__":411},"projects/projects/autoscroll-web-extension.md","AutoScroll Web Extension",{"type":22,"value":354,"toc":392},[355,357,360,362,376,378],[25,356,28],{"id":27},[30,358,359],{},"AutoScroll Web Extension is a project that automatically scrolls the page for you.",[25,361,36],{"id":35},[38,363,364,370],{},[41,365,366,369],{},[44,367,368],{},"Automated Scrolling",": Hand-free scrolling experience.",[41,371,372,375],{},[44,373,374],{},"Configurable",": Settings to adjust scroll speed and behavior.",[25,377,63],{"id":62},[38,379,380,3